## Abstract

Keyvoy  is the first dedicated wallet abstraction and developer onboarding infrastructure for Canton Network. It provides Canton application developers with production-ready TypeScript SDKs, embedded wallet provisioning, social and institutional login flows, signing policy engine, and Canton-native identity management — all through a single npm integration.

Canton Network is the only top-20 market cap blockchain ($5.7B) without a dedicated wallet infrastructure provider. Every competing L1 ecosystem has mature solutions: Privy (acquired by Stripe, 75M+ accounts), Dynamic (acquired by Fireblocks for ~$90M, 50M+ wallets), Reown/WalletConnect ($38M raised, 70K+ apps). This gap forces every Canton application builder to independently solve wallet integration, authentication, and key management from scratch — duplicating effort by 3–6 months per team, introducing security risks, and directly throttling ecosystem growth.

Keyvoy  fills this gap as shared ecosystem infrastructure using an Open Core model: the core SDK modules (authentication, wallet abstraction, Canton integration, UI components) are open-source under Apache 2.0, providing the public good that the Canton ecosystem needs, while enterprise backend services (managed signing service, analytics dashboard, premium SSO connectors) remain commercially licensed to ensure long-term sustainability. Any Canton application can integrate the open-source SDK in under 30 minutes, directly accelerating ecosystem growth, developer adoption, and Canton Coin burn through increased transaction activity.

