## Rationale

### Why is this the right approach?

**Competitive Landscape: How Keyvoy compares**

| | **Privy** (Stripe) | **Dynamic** (Fireblocks) | **Reown** (WalletConnect) | **PartyLayer Enterprise** (Canton) |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Target Chain** | EVM, Solana | EVM, Solana | EVM, Solana, Bitcoin, TON | **Canton (exclusive)** |
| **Wallets Served** | 75M+ accounts | 50M+ wallets | 35M+ unique wallets | New — first Canton wallet infra |
| **Key Management** | MPC (Shamir + secure enclaves) | TSS-MPC + passkeys | N/A (wallet connector, not key manager) | Server-side custodial v1, MPC upgrade path via `SignerProvider` |
| **Auth Methods** | Social, email, SMS, passkeys | Social, email, passkeys, SAML, OIDC | Wallet-only (no auth layer) | Social, email, SMS, OIDC, SAML 2.0 |
| **Embedded Wallets** | Yes — auto-provision on signup | Yes — auto-provision on signup | No — connects existing wallets only | **Yes — auto-provision on login with Canton party registration** |
| **Smart Contract Model** | Solidity / EVM | Solidity / EVM | Chain-agnostic connector | **DAML — Canton Ledger API native** |
| **Privacy Model** | Public chain (all state visible) | Public chain (all state visible) | Public chain | **Sub-transaction privacy, participant visibility rules** |
| **Institutional SSO** | Basic (email-domain gating) | SAML, OIDC, enterprise IdP | None | OIDC + SAML 2.0 with Canton wallet binding |
| **Compliance Tooling** | Limited | Basic audit logs | None | Audit logging, RBAC, KYC interface spec, data residency |
| **Canton Compatibility** | None — EVM-only, no DAML, no Ledger API | None — EVM-only | None — no Canton wallet support | **Native — CIP-0103 reference implementation** |
| **CIP-0104 Traffic** | N/A | N/A | N/A | **Automatic traffic metrics for app rewards** |
| **Licensing** | Proprietary SaaS | Proprietary (now Fireblocks) | Open-source protocol + commercial | **Open Core — SDK open (Apache 2.0), enterprise services commercial** |
| **Funding / Exit** | Acquired by Stripe ($41.3M raised) | Acquired by Fireblocks (~$90M) | $38M raised | Ecosystem-funded via Canton Dev Fund |

**Key takeaway:** Privy, Dynamic, and Reown are structurally incompatible with Canton. They are built for EVM — they do not support DAML, Canton Ledger API, sub-transaction privacy, or synchronization domain routing. Keyvoy is not competing with them; it is filling the gap they cannot fill. Canton needs its own native wallet infrastructure, just as Ethereum needed Privy and Solana needed Phantom.

